{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17505216","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17505216"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:27:18+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:27:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2419"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2419","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2419"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.38,0.4,0.11,0.09,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2419"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"42946"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2419","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2419"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2419"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"27923"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"768"},{"type":"tags","id":"1309"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"6352"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1818"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1819"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1830"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42488"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43147"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"42946","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/42946"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 23-year-old woman attends the Emergency Department with a sore right ankle, sustained when she tripped and fell over earlier that day. She reports that she has been unable to bear any weight on that foot since her injury. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, the patient appears well with observations within the normal ranges. She is unable to weight bear. Focussed examination shows no evident bony deformity with soft tissue swelling over the lateral malleolus. Active and passive movement is restricted due to pain and there is tenderness on palpation over the lateral malleolus. Based on these findings, an X-ray is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate plan of management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Non weight-bearing and crutches","Walking boot","Open reduction and plating","Cylinder plaster","Compression screw"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has a non-displaced Weber A lateral malleolus fracture. These injuries are most commonly managed with a combination of immobilisation in either a short-leg walking cast or a \u003Cstrong\u003Ewalking boot\u003C/strong\u003E (colloquially referred to as a \u0027moon boot\u0027). Patients are encouraged to progressively weight bear on the affected foot over six weeks.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-weight-bearing and crutches \u003C/strong\u003Eis common management for soft-tissue injury such as strains of the anterior talofibular ligament. In this patient\u0027s case, it is important to immobilise the range of motion of the ankle with a walking boot.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOpen reduction and plating \u003C/strong\u003Eand \u003Cstrong\u003Ecompression screws\u003C/strong\u003E are forms of operative management reserved for Weber C and some Weber B ankle fractures. This patient\u0027s injury does not indicate for operative management.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECylinder plasters\u003C/strong\u003E do not immobilise the foot and ankle and are therefore inappropriate for the management of ankle fractures.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Minimally displace ankle fractures are typically managed conservatively."],"references":["Aiyer AA, Zachwieja EC, Lawrie CM, Kaplan JRM. Management of Isolated Lateral Malleolus Fractures. J Am Acad Orthop Surg. 2019;27(2):50-59. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30278012/","Javed OA, Javed QA, Ukoumunne OC, Di Mascio L. Surgical versus conservative management of ankle fractures in adults: A systematic review and meta-analysis. Foot Ankle Surg. 2020;26(7):723-735. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31818542/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"27923"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2419"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"14926"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"14926","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/14926"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/33575913-d992-4ae6-81ad-5a1ca76e4bd3.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/33575913-d992-4ae6-81ad-5a1ca76e4bd3.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":318,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"27923","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/27923"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-02-26T11:06:31+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-09-25T16:55:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2419"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"42946"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings"